{"questionId":"2597568","questionHtml":"<p>The angle between a line and a plane is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>α</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>.</p>\n<p>The equation of the line is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>z</mi></math>,&nbsp;and the equation of the plane is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>)</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>)</mo><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Find the value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>direction vector of the line is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp;(seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>normal vector of the plane is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp;(seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>correct scalar product <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi></math> (seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>one correct magnitude (seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>16</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mfenced><msqrt><mn>17</mn></msqrt></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msqrt><mn>9</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mfenced><msqrt><mn>14</mn></msqrt></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>recognizing angle between normal and direction vector is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>α</mi></math>&nbsp;(seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>angle&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>α</mi></math>&nbsp;may be implied by use of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi></math>&nbsp;on the RHS of the step below&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>attempt to substitute into the formula for the angle between two vectors to form an&nbsp;equation in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>17</mn></msqrt><msqrt><mn>14</mn></msqrt><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>α</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>17</mn></msqrt><msqrt><mn>14</mn></msqrt><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>correct expression for the magnitude of the vector product</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>cos</mi><mi>α</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;(seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;one correct magnitude (seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>16</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi></msqrt><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>17</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msqrt><mn>9</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></msqrt><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>14</mn></msqrt><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>recognizing angle between normal and direction vector is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>α</mi></math> (seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;angle&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>α</mi></math>&nbsp;may be implied by use of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi></math>&nbsp;on the RHS of the step below</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>attempt to substitute into the formula for the angle between two vectors to form an&nbsp;equation in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>17</mn></msqrt><msqrt><mn>14</mn></msqrt><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>α</mi><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; OR</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>17</mn></msqrt><msqrt><mn>14</mn></msqrt><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>932389</mn><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>932</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;Award maximum&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)(A1)(A1)(A1)(M1)(M1)A0</strong></em>&nbsp;for a correct answer given&nbsp;in degrees&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>54</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4219</mn><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo> </mo><mo>°</mo></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[7 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2597568","referenceCode":"23M.2.AHL.TZ1.8","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"The angle between a line and a plane is α, where α∈ℝ, 0<α<π2. The equation of the line is x-13=y+22=5-z, and the equation of the plane is 4x+(cos α)y+(sin α)z=1. Find the value of ","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"8","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.13—Scalar (dot) product","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.18—Intersections of lines & planes"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}